table.name: installation
table.remarks: This is the base table for all installation types.

table.name: leak
table.remarks: pipe leaks

table.name: meter
table.remarks: Table for meters. Inherits from node.

table.name: meter_reference
table.remarks: Table for meter references. These are used to place references to meters if they rely far away from their pipe (i.e. on another printed map). Hence, the reference is printed on the same map than the pipe.

table.name: network_element
table.remarks: Tables for network network_elements. Every network_element of the network (hydrants, network_element, installations, etc.) inherit from network_element which itself inherits from node.

column.name: orientation
column.remarks: orientation field aims at overwrtiting qwat_od.node._pipe_orientation which is automatically calculated from the pipes. In the editable views, orientation will be COALESCE(netwrok_element.orientation, node._pipe_orientation). Update will be forwarded to network_element.

table.name: node
table.remarks: Tables for network nodes. Every element of the network (hydrants, valves, element, installations, etc.) inherit from element which itself inherits from node. Node should only contain geometric fields and automatic attributes (district, pressurezone, printmaps, etc).

table.name: part
table.remarks: Table for installation parts. Inherits from node.

table.name: pipe
table.remarks: Table for pipes.

table.name: pressurezone
table.remarks: Pressure zones.

table.name: printmap
table.remarks: This table is used for polygons for predefined printable maps. shortname would be used as label string, and long_mame would be used in the print composer.

table.name: remote
table.remarks: Table for installation remotes.

table.name: samplingpoint
table.remarks: Table for sampling points. Inherits from node.

table.name: subscriber
table.remarks: Table for subscriber. Inherits from node.

table.name: subscriber_reference
table.remarks: Table for subscriber references. These are used to place references to subscribers if they rely far away from their pipe (i.e. on another printed map). Hence, the reference is printed on the same map than the pipe.

table.name: surveypoint
table.remarks: Table for sampling points. Inherits from surveypoint.

table.name: valve
table.remarks: Table for valve.

table.name: vw_pipe_schema
table.remarks: Final view for schema

table.name: vw_pipe_schema_error
table.remarks: Report IDs of parent pipe where pipe concatenation leads to a MultiLineString and not to a LineString or if an infinite referencing loop has been detected.

table.name: vw_pipe_schema_visibleitems
table.remarks: visible pipe in the schematic view (before merge)

table.name: vw_valve_lines
table.remarks: Valves represented as lines. Each line is made from two points, the handle as starting point and the location on the pipe as ending point.
